30. How do you locate elements in Selenium WebDriver?
- Use locators : ID, NAME, CLASS_NAME, TAG_NAME, LINK_TEXT, PARTIAL_LINK_TEXT, CSS_SELECTOR, XPATH
- Single element -> driver.find_element(By.ID , "id")
- Multiple elements -> driver.find_elements(By.NAME, "name")
- Returns first matching element for "find_element"
- Raises NoSuchElementException if element not found

31. How do you interact with elements in Selenium WebDriver?
- Type text -> element.send_keys("Hello")
- Clear text -> element.clear()
- Click element -> element.click()
- Keyboard actions -> element.send_keys(Keys.ARROW_DOWN) (or other keys like enter, tab)

32. How do you handle iframes in Selenium?
- Switch to iframe
    driver.switch_to.frame(iframe_element)
    - can switch by index, name/id or WebElement
- Interact with elements inside the iframe
    Use normal webdriver commands (click(), send_keys(),etc..)
- Switch back to main page
    driver.switch_to.default_content()
- Example
    iframe = driver.driver.find_element(By.TAG_NAME, "iframe")
    driver.switch_to.iframe(iframe)
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "username").send_keys("test")
    driver.switch_to.default_content()
- You cannot access iframe elements without switching to it first

33. How do you locate multiple elements in Selenium WebDriver?
- Use "find_elements()" to get list of matching elements
    elements = driver.find_elements(By.TAG_NAME, "a")
- Difference from find_element()
    - find_element() -> Returns single element; raises NoSuchElementException if not found
    - find_elements() -> Returns list of elements; returns empty list [] if None found
- Always handle empty lists to avoid errors when using find_elements().

34. What are the locator strategies to find multiple elements?
- By.NAME -> Find elements by "name" attribute
    driver.find_elements(By.NAME , "value")
- By.XPATH -> Find elements using XPATH expressions
    driver.find_elements(By.XPATH , "//tag[@attribute='value'])
- By.LINK_TEXT -> Exact match of hyperlink text
- By.PARTIAL_LINK_TEXT -> Partial match of hyperlink text
- By.TAG_NAME -> Find elements by class attribute
- By.CLASS_NAME -> Find elements by class attribute
- By.CSS_SELECTOR -> Find elements using CSS selectors (fast and flexible, preferred in modern automation)
- Always pick the unique and stable locator to avoid flaky tests

35. What happens if no elements are found with find_elements()?
- Returns empty list []
- Does not raise an exception (unlike find_element() which raises "NoSuchElementException")
- Always check if the list is empty before iterating to avoid errors

